Description: Fragment of oval handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora to sharpish turn. Clay fine pink-brown. Circular stamp with rose symbol. Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Name Aleximachos. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0046,02. Trimmed.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0989)
